18/01/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- The Turkish government approved the sending of three helicopters to the NATO-led International Stabilisation Force in Afghanistan (ISAF), Deputy Chief of General Staff General Ilker Basbug said Friday (16 January).
He added that the helicopters would depart for Kabul once the technical talks on the issue were completed.
The Netherlands and Germany would also contribute to ISAF with five helicopters and three helicopters respectively.
(Anadolu Agency, AFP - 16/01/04)
